# Event 1000 (onJoinGame)

macro.help.event.onjoingame.line[0]=&f<onJoinGame>
macro.help.event.onjoingame.line[1]=This event is raised whenever you join a game (single player or
macro.help.event.onjoingame.line[2]=SMP) and can be used to start background macros or issue
macro.help.event.onjoingame.line[3]=server commands when joining a new game.

# Event 1001 (onChat)

macro.help.event.onchat.line[0]=&f<onChat>
macro.help.event.onchat.line[1]=This event is raised whenever a new chat message arrives from
macro.help.event.onchat.line[2]=the server. You can access the message that was received using
macro.help.event.onchat.line[3]=the &cCHAT&6 variable within the event.

# Event 1002 (onHealthChange)

macro.help.event.onhealthchange.line[0]=&f<onHealthChange>
macro.help.event.onhealthchange.line[1]=This event is raised whenever your health level changes eg. when
macro.help.event.onhealthchange.line[2]=you take damage or receive health from food or potions. Each
macro.help.event.onhealthchange.line[3]=heart represents 2 health points so the maximum health is 20. You
macro.help.event.onhealthchange.line[4]=can access the current level using the &cHEALTH&6 global variable.

# Event 1003 (onFoodChange)

macro.help.event.onfoodchange.line[0]=&f<onFoodChange>
macro.help.event.onfoodchange.line[1]=This event is raised whenever your food bar level changes. Each
macro.help.event.onfoodchange.line[2]=food icon represents 2 food points so the maximum food level
macro.help.event.onfoodchange.line[3]=is 20. You can access the current food level using the &cHUNGER
macro.help.event.onfoodchange.line[4]=global variable.

# Event 1004 (onArmourChange)

macro.help.event.onarmourchange.line[0]=&f<onArmourChange>
macro.help.event.onarmourchange.line[1]=Raised whenever your armour level changes, for example when you
macro.help.event.onarmourchange.line[2]=take damage or put on a new piece of armour. Each armour icon
macro.help.event.onarmourchange.line[3]=represents 2 armour points so the maximum armour level is 20.
macro.help.event.onarmourchange.line[4]=Get the current armour level using the &cARMOUR&6 global variable.

# Event 1005 (onWorldChange)

macro.help.event.onworldchange.line[0]=&f<onWorldChange>
macro.help.event.onworldchange.line[1]=This event is raised when the world changes, for example when
macro.help.event.onworldchange.line[2]=travelling between worlds in multi-world servers or travelling
macro.help.event.onworldchange.line[3]=between Surface, Nether and End.

# Event 1006 (onModeChange)

macro.help.event.onmodechange.line[0]=&f<onModeChange>
macro.help.event.onmodechange.line[1]=This event is raised when your game mode changes, for example
macro.help.event.onmodechange.line[2]=when switching from creative to survival.

# Event 1007 (onInventorySlotChange)

macro.help.event.oninventoryslotchange.line[0]=&f<onInventorySlotChange>
macro.help.event.oninventoryslotchange.line[1]=This event is raised when the selected inventory slot is changed.
macro.help.event.oninventoryslotchange.line[2]=The previously-selected slot can be accessed using the
macro.help.event.oninventoryslotchange.line[3]=&cOLDINVSLOT&6 variable within the event.

# Event 1008 (onOxygenChange)

macro.help.event.onoxygenchange.line[0]=&f<onOxygenChange>
macro.help.event.onoxygenchange.line[1]=This event is raised when your oxygen level changes. The oxygen
macro.help.event.onoxygenchange.line[2]=level represents the number of ticks that you can breathe
macro.help.event.onoxygenchange.line[3]=underwater before beginning to drown and the current level can
macro.help.event.onoxygenchange.line[4]=be accessed using the &cOXYGEN&6 global variable.

# Event 1009 (onXPChange)

macro.help.event.onxpchange.line[0]=&f<onXPChange>
macro.help.event.onxpchange.line[1]=This event is raised when your experience level changes. You
macro.help.event.onxpchange.line[2]=can access the current XP level using the &cTOTALXP&6 and &cXP&6
macro.help.event.onxpchange.line[3]=global variables.

# Event 1010 (onLevelChange)

macro.help.event.onlevelchange.line[0]=&f<onLevelChange>
macro.help.event.onlevelchange.line[1]=This event is raised when your level changes, you can access
macro.help.event.onlevelchange.line[2]=the current level using the &cLEVEL&6 global variable.

# Event 1011 (onItemDurabilityChange)

macro.help.event.onitemdurabilitychange.line[0]=&f<onItemDurabilityChange>
macro.help.event.onitemdurabilitychange.line[1]=This event is raised when the currently-wielded item's durability
macro.help.event.onitemdurabilitychange.line[2]=level changes. Different items have different durability amounts
macro.help.event.onitemdurabilitychange.line[3]=and change durability at different times. You can access the
macro.help.event.onitemdurabilitychange.line[4]=level of the current item using the &cDURABILITY&6 variable.

# Event 1012 (onWeatherChange)

macro.help.event.onweatherchange.line[0]=&f<onWeatherChange>
macro.help.event.onweatherchange.line[1]=This event is raised when the current weather level changes.
macro.help.event.onweatherchange.line[2]=You can access the current rain strength using the &cRAIN&6
macro.help.event.onweatherchange.line[3]=global variable.

# Event 1013 (onPickupItem)

macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[0]=&f<onPickupItem>
macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[1]=This event is raised when an item is picked up by the player.
macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[2]=You can access the item id of the collected item using the
macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[3]=&cPICKUPID&6 variable, the name of the collected item using the
macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[4]=&cPICKUPITEM&6 variable, and the number of items collected
macro.help.event.onpickupitem.line[5]=using the &cPICKUPAMOUNT&6 variable within the event.

# Event 1014 (onPlayerJoined)

macro.help.event.onplayerjoined.line[0]=&f<onPlayerJoined>
macro.help.event.onplayerjoined.line[1]=This event is raised when a new player joins the server in a
macro.help.event.onplayerjoined.line[2]=multiplayer game. You can access the name of the new player
macro.help.event.onplayerjoined.line[3]=using the &cJOINEDPLAYER&6 variable within the event.

# Event 1015 (onShowGui)

macro.help.event.onshowgui.line[0]=&f<onShowGui>
macro.help.event.onshowgui.line[1]=This event is raised when the current Minecraft GUI changes. You
macro.help.event.onshowgui.line[2]=can access the class name of displayed GUI using the &cGUI&6
macro.help.event.onshowgui.line[3]=global variable, the variable is set to "NONE" when no GUI is
macro.help.event.onshowgui.line[4]=currently displayed.

# Event 1016 (onArmourDurabilityChange)

macro.help.event.onarmourdurabilitychange.line[0]=&f<onArmourDurabilityChange>
macro.help.event.onarmourdurabilitychange.line[1]=This event is raised when any currently-worn armour durability
macro.help.event.onarmourdurabilitychange.line[2]=level changes. Different items have different durability amounts
macro.help.event.onarmourdurabilitychange.line[3]=and change durability at different times.

# Event 1017 (onAutoCraftingComplete)

macro.help.event.onautocraftingcomplete.line[0]=&f<onAutoCraftingComplete>
macro.help.event.onautocraftingcomplete.line[1]=This event is raised when an auto-crafting process is completed.
macro.help.event.onautocraftingcomplete.line[2]=The reason for crafting being completed can be accessed
macro.help.event.onautocraftingcomplete.line[3]=through the &cREASON&6 variable within the event.

# Event 1018 (onConfigChange)

macro.help.event.onconfigchange.line[0]=&f<onConfigChange>
macro.help.event.onconfigchange.line[1]=This event is raised when the active configuration is changed.
macro.help.event.onconfigchange.line[2]=The name of the new configuration is available via the &cCONFIG
macro.help.event.onconfigchange.line[3]=variable within the event. &c&lNote that this event will be
macro.help.event.onconfigchange.line[4]=&c&lraised in the &nnew&r &c&lconfig &nnot the old one!

# Event 1020 (onSendChatMessage)

macro.help.event.onsendchatmessage.line[0]=&f<onSendChatMessage>
macro.help.event.onsendchatmessage.line[1]=This event is raised whenever a new chat message is sent in the
macro.help.event.onsendchatmessage.line[2]=You can access the message that was typed the &cCHAT&6 variable
macro.help.event.onsendchatmessage.line[3]=within the event.

